items.name: NPR Style Model
items.description:
NPR (Non-Photorealistic Rendering), also known as expressive or hand-drawn rendering, is a technique that simulates hand-drawn or cartoonish effects in two-dimensional or three-dimensional scenes rather than creating realistic photographic effects like traditional rendering techniques. For example, NPR technology was used in "The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild" to create a dreamlike visual experience. Due to the unique style created by NPR, some artists intentionally pursue and emulate NPR effects in their works, appreciating the non-photorealistic and artistic expression it offers. Therefore, NPR technology is also considered a means of creation and expression, providing artists with more creative space and inspiration.

However, implementing NPR requires specific rendering algorithms, which often necessitate the creation of custom shaders. Developing shaders requires a certain degree of computer graphics and programming knowledge, which may be daunting for artists who need more relevant backgrounds. Moreover, writing shaders requires a solid mathematical foundation in linear algebra, calculus, and other mathematical concepts, specific hardware and software support, and repeated experimentation and debugging, all of which make shader development quite challenging.

In light of these challenges, this paper proposes using deep learning to train an NPR-style model as a feasible solution for NPR rendering. Taking the typical three-to-two technique in NPR as an example, we prepare a complete dataset, train the LoRA model, evaluate its performance, and optimize it through various steps to obtain a model that can simulate the three-to-two style effectively. The results show that the model has a good fit and high robustness. This research provides a new perspective for achieving NPR style and may inspire further research.

items.name: art by Chen Uen
items.description:
It would be great if you could share your works using this LoRA with me!

CHEN UEN - an Asian treasure

His style combines Chinese ink painting techniques with Western painting skills, which are both delicate and bold, and full of heroic and chivalrous spirit.

CHEN UEN (December 27, 1958 - March 26, 2017), was a Taiwanese comic book artist and illustrator. He was born in Daxi Township, Taoyuan County, Taiwan . He graduated from the Sculpture Department of Fu Hsin Trade and Arts School. CHEN UEN was known for his comic book artwork in ink style, and gained recognition for his works Assassin Legend and Abi Sword in his early career. In 1990, he published the comic book Eastern Heroes in Japan, which was praised as "an Asian treasure" and awarded the "Excellent Award" by the Japan Cartoonists Association. He passed away on March 26, 2017, at the age of 58 due to a myocardial infarction.

Introduction

This is a LyCORIS of Mejiro Ardan from "Umamusum Pretty Deby". The difference between other similar characters Lora is the addition of Neige √âmeraude. Using the cut off pluginÔºà https://github.com/hnmr293/sd-webui-cutoff Ôºâto prevent elemental pollution will achieve better results.

Example images are generated by Viewermix model.

Usage

Suggest using a weight of around 0.75.

During the marking process, in order to isolate element contamination, a method of setting keywords separately for each card surface was adopted. The following are the keywords for each vertical drawing:

Casual clothes: mejiro_ ardan_ CA

Neige √âmeraudeÔºömejiro_ ardan_ NE

Training Details

Using NAI Final as the base model for training, approximately 500 images were used as the training set, and about half of the images were used as the regression training set. Each image was repeated 10 times for 10 epochs, with a final step count of 5150.

The following are the main settings parameters:

network_ dim=32

network_ alpha=32

keep_ tokens=8

conv_ dim=4

conv_ alpha=4

lr="1e-4"

unet_ lr="1e-4"

text_ encoder_ lr="1e-5"

batch_ size = 2

Limitations

Introduction

This is a LyCORIS of Mejiro Ardan from "Umamusum Pretty Deby". The difference between other similar characters Lora is the addition of Neige √âmeraude. Using the cut off pluginÔºà https://github.com/hnmr293/sd-webui-cutoff Ôºâto prevent elemental pollution will achieve better results.

Example images are generated by Viewermix model.

Usage

Suggest using a weight of around 0.75.

During the marking process, in order to isolate element contamination, a method of setting keywords separately for each card surface was adopted. The following are the keywords for each vertical drawing:

Casual clothesÔºösakura_laurel_CA

Teresan uniformÔºösakura_laurel_UN

ShobofukuÔºösakura_laure_SF

ÔºàI missed the latter "l" when taggingÔºâ

othersÔºösakura_laurel

Training Details

Using NAI Final as the base model for training, approximately 50 images were used as the training set, and about half of the images were used as the regression training set. Each image was repeated 10 times for 10 epochs, with a final step count of 1500.

The following are the main settings parameters:

network_ dim=32

network_ alpha=32

keep_ tokens=8

conv_ dim=4

conv_ alpha=4

lr="1e-4"

unet_ lr="1e-4"

text_ encoder_ lr="1e-5"

batch_ size = 2

Limitations

  1. It is very hard to draw the asymmetrical designs in character portraits. Maybe a lot of tries and manual assistance is a certain way to achieve good results.

  2. During the process of presenting the example image, I did not notice that the Additional Network plugin was invalid, and some LyCORIS layers did not output, which may have an impact on the final result.

items.name: poison ivy
items.description:
DC's Poison Ivy. Made purely as a test, but it seems to work pretty consistently so I might as well upload it!

Trained on a SFW database of 51 images @ 40 epochs 1 repeat for a total of 2,040 steps on sd1.5. Seems to work perfectly fine on strength 1.

Trigger word: poison ivy
The addition of long hair, red hair, green eyes keeps a consistent look.

The leaves and green colour on her clothes are apparent from pretty low weights, but can be accentuated or removed with the prompt 'leaf'. I've had success with combining it with different clothing articles [leaf|bikini] [leaf|leotard] [leaf|dress] so feel free to experiment. Seems flexible enough to prompt in other clothes, but just have a look at the training data to see what you want to include/avoid.

Feedback, criticisms welcome! Leave a like or a review, or don't I can't tell you what to do.

items.name: RGBjanine
items.description:
This is my first Lora model which I have generated using the collab drive. I noticed that there was a lot of Anime here and I thought to myself that it would be nice to throw some Real Ghostbusters into the mix, so I decided to learn how to make a Lora based on Janine Melnitz from The Real Ghostbusters cartoon, which was also considered an anime in the 80s. I have uploaded various test images of me seeing how it interacts with other models. It seems that you have to describe the clothing colors a bit to try to get her in her usual attire but other than that, the face and hairstyle seem to be spot-on to me, which is great.

There really aren't any clear shots of the character as seen in the old cartoon series, so what I had to do was boot up some of my old DVDs (which came from the studio VHS copies) pick screenshots, and then completely redraw those screenshots from scratch while staying true to the look of the character. I think I must have drawn at least ten of them. Those drawings became the source content for Lora.

Please post things that you guys make with this Lora so I can see check it out and don't forget to like and comment. If you guys like it, I may move into bringing the other characters over (which will take some time to draw them all out that way they are clean without the ghosting of VHS lines and colors that are in the DVDs). I may also make plans to do the characters from another great anime called Akira!

**NOTE ** As an AI Art newbie who is very interested in "How" this stuff works, especially the scientific side of it, I really wish that there was a way to get a full-blown forum going on here at Civitai where we can all talk about models, share techniques, post stuff, etc. I think it would be great because I love the site, but that would be the cherry on top to see Civitai turn into a community!

The trigger word is 'Holding_Sign'.

It is recommended to add 'text' and 'writing' to negative prompt. This LoRA was trained only on blank white signs, but the model may interfere.

This LoRA was trained on a mix of realistic and anime stock images of people holding signs, as well as 'girl holding sign' meme templates.

At high weights it may make your character look slightly younger/more moe. I have done my best to minimize this, it was very strong in version 1 and 2) this is version 3, and much better). Please add appropriate tags to negative prompt to avoid this if you desire. I will try to reduce this further in future.
